ZH: 智慧是成功的基石。
EN: Wisdom is the cornerstone of success.

ZH: 他的智慧使得他能够做出正确的决定。
EN: His wisdom enables him to make the right decisions.

ZH: 学习能够培养智慧。
EN: Studying can cultivate wisdom.

ZH: 智慧的人懂得如何运用知识。
EN: Wise people know how to use their knowledge.

ZH: 智慧并非凭空而来，而是通过经验和教训获得的。
EN: Wisdom does not come out of thin air, but through experiences and lessons.

ZH: 这个问题需要一些智慧来解决。
EN: This problem requires some wisdom to solve.

ZH: 智慧是我们最宝贵的财富之一。
EN: Wisdom is one of our most precious treasures.

ZH: 他的智慧使得他在困境中找到了出路。
EN: His wisdom helped him find a way out of the predicament.

ZH: 深思熟虑是智慧的表现之一。
EN: Thoughtfulness is one of the manifestations of wisdom.

ZH: 智慧就像一把钥匙，能够打开机遇的大门。
EN: Wisdom is like a key that can unlock the doors of opportunities.

ZH: 智慧的人能够从失败中汲取经验教训。
EN: Wise people can learn from their failures.

ZH: 具备智慧是成为一个优秀领导者的要素之一。
EN: Having wisdom is one of the key elements to becoming an excellent leader.

ZH: 智慧的人常常能够预见问题并设法解决。
EN: Wise people often anticipate problems and find ways to solve them.

ZH: 智慧源于知识与洞察力的结合。
EN: Wisdom comes from the combination of knowledge and insight.

ZH: 学习如何思考是获得智慧的重要途径之一。
EN: Learning how to think is one important way to acquire wisdom.

ZH: 智慧是通过不断反思和自我改进获得的。
EN: Wisdom is acquired through continuous self-reflection and self-improvement.

ZH: 智慧使得我们能够做出明智的决策。
EN: Wisdom enables us to make wise decisions.

ZH: 拥有智慧的人更容易解决问题。
EN: People with wisdom find it easier to solve problems.

ZH: 智慧使得我们能够在困难时保持乐观态度。
EN: Wisdom enables us to maintain a positive attitude in times of difficulty.

ZH: 智慧的人懂得如何与人相处和处理复杂的关系。
EN: Wise people know how to interact with others and handle complex relationships.
